    "abstract": "<jats:title>\n                  A\n                  <jats:sc>bstract</jats:sc>\n                </jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The aim of this paper is to model COVID-19 based on Markov chains. First, we introduce basic concepts of Markov chains with examples from different disciplines. Second, we use different types of Markov chains to model COVID-19, including confirmed cases, death and recovered cases and forecasting future confirmed cases. Third, we give conclusions based on these models and ideas for future work.</jats:p>",
